snippet.textDisplay: The practice of collecting alms is a part of Sannyasa (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sannyasa). It aims at breaking the person's Ahamkara (Ego & Pride), thereby making him a better human being. It also serves as a way of sustenance for the monks since they study and educate society through their knowledge, which doesn't earn them a living. Furthermore, it gives a sense & satisfaction of doing a good deed to the giver.

snippet.textDisplay:
Myanmar practice Theravada Buddhism so they are not so extreme about meat. Mahayana doesn't eat it. Even Buddha didn't refuse the meat that ppl donate, he accepted everything even if he might not eat. It's another evil monk who refused and turn the bowl down to show that he only takes vegetables. This is how "Tabake mauk" which has the meaning of "protest" derived from.

Monks don't go out in the rainy season, they call it "Wah twin" they stay inside the monasteries then after that period ppl make huge donation to monks "Ka htain". Buddhists don't get married during that season. I don't know the reason, I'm just their christian neighbor.
